<h2 id="buttons">Buttons</h2>

<p>Use spinners within buttons to indicate an action is currently processing or taking place. You may also swap the text out of the spinner element and utilize button text as needed.</p>

<div class="bd-example-wrapper">
    <ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
        <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
            <a class="nav-link active" data-toggle="tab" href="#result-324" role="tab" aria-controls="result-324" aria-selected="true">Result</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
            <a class="nav-link" data-toggle="tab" href="#html-324" role="tab" aria-controls="html-324" aria-selected="false">HTML Code</a>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="tab-content" id="examplte-tab-content-324">
        <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="result-324" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="result-324"><div class="bd-example">
<button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" disabled="">
  <span class="spinner-border spinner-border-sm" role="status" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="sr-only">Loading...</span>
</button>
<button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" disabled="">
  <span class="spinner-border spinner-border-sm" role="status" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  Loading...
</button>
</div></div>
